Usage: pyloc.py directory

Where directory is the directory to scan.

Example output:

$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

PYLOC
-----
Folder   : /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

Language : Shell
        Files         : 1
        Code lines    : 12
        Comment lines : 1
        Whitespace    : 4

        Physical SLOC : 17

Language : Haskell
        Files         : 15
        Code lines    : 1326
        Comment lines : 150
        Whitespace    : 282

        Physical SLOC : 1758

TOTAL physical SLOC : 1775

